w:r.w:t: The following checklist is designed with the (ideal) timetable of twelve months. If youre planning your wedding on a shorter schedule, just start at the beginning of the list, and try to catch up as quickly as possible. Use the boxes to the left of the items to check off tasks as you complete them.
Discuss the size, style, and location.
Choose the members of your wedding party.
Choose a wedding date and time.
Hire a photographer and a videographer.
Visit and reserve wedding and reception sites.
Start compiling your guest to estimate total.
Begin shopping for the wedding gown.
Reserve hotel rooms for out-of-town guests.
Do a hair and makeup run-through.
Confirm all transportation plans for before and after wedding.
Mail the invitations 8 weeks prior to wedding day.
Order tuxedoes for the groom and groomsmen.
Meet with the caterer to go over menus.
Have final fitting for wedding gown.
Book a hotel room for the wedding night.
If writing vows, work on them now.
Purchase gifts for the wedding attendants.
Look into where bridal party will get ready.
Plan for any fees due on the wedding day.
Find someone to solve last minute issues.
Give the caterer a final head count.
Give bridal party and parents their gift.
Hand off rings to best man or ring bearer.
Allow at least two hours to get dressed.
Post wedding announcements in the mail.
